# AURA — Smart Traffic & Pollution Analysis
## Complete Setup Guide with Real Datasets

---

## 📁 Project Structure
```
aura_full/
├── module1_detection/
│   └── detector.py            ← YOLOv8 + OpenCV (video/frames/webcam)
├── module2_prediction/
│   └── aqi_predictor.py       ← Random Forest AQI prediction
├── module3_dashboard/
│   └── dashboard.py           ← Streamlit live dashboard
├── utils/
│   └── generate_dataset.py    ← Synthetic frame generator (included)
├── data/
│   └── sample_frames/         ← 200 generated CCTV frames (ready to use)
├── outputs/
│   ├── tdi_results.csv        ← Module 1 output (vehicle counts per frame)
│   ├── aura_rf_model.pkl      ← Trained Random Forest
│   ├── aura_scaler.pkl        ← Feature scaler
│   ├── model_meta.json        ← Model metrics
│   └── plots/
│       └── aura_model_results.png
└── requirements.txt
```

---

## 🗂️ Real Datasets (Free & Publicly Available)

### Traffic Videos — Use with Module 1:

| Dataset | Link | Size | Format |
|---|---|---|---|
| Highway Traffic Videos (City Univ HK) | https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/aryashah2k/highway-traffic-videos-dataset | 88 MB | MP4 (254 clips) |
| Traffic Video Dataset | https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/arshadrahmanziban/traffic-video-dataset | ~200 MB | MP4 |
| Road Traffic Video Monitoring | https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/shawon10/road-traffic-video-monitoring | ~50 MB | MP4 |
| Roboflow Traffic Detection | https://universe.roboflow.com/yolo-iuil0/traffic-4zbse | ~300 MB | Images + YOLO labels |
| HuggingFace Real-Time Traffic | https://huggingface.co/datasets/UniDataPro/real-time-traffic-video-dataset | 500 videos | MP4 + COCO JSON |

### AQI / Pollution Data — Use with Module 2:

| Dataset | Link | Format |
|---|---|---|
| CPCB Hourly AQI | https://cpcb.nic.in/automatic-monitoring-data/ | CSV per city |
| data.gov.in AQI | https://data.gov.in/resource/real-time-air-quality-index | CSV/API |
| AQICN World AQI | https://aqicn.org/data-platform/token/ | JSON API |
| OpenAQ Platform | https://openaq.org/ | API / CSV |

---

## ⚙️ Installation

```bash
# Install all dependencies
pip install ultralytics opencv-python scikit-learn pandas numpy \
            matplotlib joblib streamlit plotly

# Ultralytics auto-downloads YOLOv8n.pt on first run (~6 MB)
```

---

## 🚀 Step-by-Step Usage

### STEP 1 — Run Traffic Detection (Module 1)

```bash
cd aura_full

# Option A: Use included synthetic frames (no video needed)
python module1_detection/detector.py --source data/sample_frames --mode json

# Option B: Use a real video file (requires ultralytics)
python module1_detection/detector.py --source /path/to/traffic.mp4

# Option C: Live webcam
python module1_detection/detector.py --source 0

# Option D: Roboflow image folder (YOLO mode)
python module1_detection/detector.py --source /path/to/roboflow/images --mode yolo
```
→ Output: `outputs/tdi_results.csv` (TDI per frame)

---

### STEP 2 — Train AQI Prediction Model (Module 2)

```bash
python module2_prediction/aqi_predictor.py
```
→ Reads `outputs/tdi_results.csv` (from Module 1)  
→ Uses CPCB AQI patterns (or your real CPCB CSV)  
→ Output: `outputs/aura_rf_model.pkl` + `outputs/plots/aura_model_results.png`

**To use real CPCB data:** Edit `aqi_predictor.py` line 27:
```python
CPCB_CSV = "path/to/your_cpcb_data.csv"
# Expected columns: datetime, pm25, station, city
```

---

### STEP 3 — Launch Dashboard (Module 3)

```bash
streamlit run module3_dashboard/dashboard.py
```
→ Opens at `http://localhost:8501`  
→ Reads from `outputs/tdi_results.csv` + `outputs/aura_rf_model.pkl`  
→ Live AQI/TDI charts, hotspot map, rerouting engine  

---

## 🔁 Full Data Flow

```
[Real CCTV / Kaggle Video / Synthetic Frames]
              │
              ▼
  ┌─────────────────────────┐
  │  Module 1 — YOLOv8      │  pip install ultralytics
  │  • Load video frames    │
  │  • Detect vehicles      │  Classes: car, truck, bus,
  │    per frame            │    motorcycle, autorickshaw
  │  • Compute TDI          │  TDI = vehicles / norm_area
  │  • Save CSV             │
  └──────────┬──────────────┘
             │ tdi_results.csv
             ▼
  ┌─────────────────────────┐
  │  Module 2 — Random      │  scikit-learn
  │  Forest Regressor       │
  │  • Merge TDI + AQI      │  Features: TDI, lag-PM2.5,
  │  • Engineer features    │    wind, humidity, temp,
  │  • Train RF (300 trees) │    cyclic hour encoding
  │  • Predict PM2.5 (1h)   │  MAE ≈ 19 µg/m³, R²≈0.50
  │  • Save model .pkl      │
  └──────────┬──────────────┘
             │ aura_rf_model.pkl
             ▼
  ┌─────────────────────────┐
  │  Module 3 — Streamlit   │  streamlit + plotly
  │  Dashboard              │
  │  • Live TDI + AQI       │  Auto-refreshes every 3s
  │  • Actual vs Predicted  │  Delhi NCR hotspot map
  │  • Hotspot map          │  Rerouting trigger > threshold
  │  • Smart Rerouting      │  Google Maps API slot ready
  └─────────────────────────┘
```

---

## 🧠 Random Forest Model Details

| Parameter | Value |
|---|---|
| Algorithm | RandomForestRegressor |
| n_estimators | 300 |
| max_depth | 14 |
| max_features | sqrt |
| OOB Score (R²) | 0.923 |
| Features (18 total) | TDI, lag-PM2.5 (1/2/3/6h), rolling mean (4h/8h), hour_sin/cos, weekday, month, wind, humidity, temp |
| Target | PM2.5 one hour ahead |
| Split | 80/20 time-ordered |

---

## 🔀 Rerouting Logic

```python
# Module 3 triggers rerouting when:
if predicted_pm25 > aqi_threshold:   # default = 180 µg/m³ (CPCB "Moderate" boundary)
    activate_rerouting(zone=current_zone)
    
